<help mldsearch>

mob long description search

This function allows you to search for mobs with long descriptions
matching a perl compatible regular expression.


Syntax:  mldsearch 'pattern'

Modifiers: All modifiers should be enclosed in (? ):
(?i) case insensitive matching.
(?m) multi-line matching. (changes meaning of $ anchor to eoln)

Examples:

To find all mobs with "anitre" or "Anitre" in their description.
mldsearch '(?i)anitre'

To find all mobs whose description ends with darkling.
mldsearch 'darkling$'

<color=red>
See Also:  osdsearch oldsearch msdsearch
</color></help>
